The White House announced that it will be hosting its first ever Twitter town hall on July 6th. Twitter co-founder Jack Dorsey will moderate a conversation between President Obama and Americans about the economy and jobs. Twitter users can submit questions using the hashtag #AskObama. The White House also announced its first "Tweetup," where a portion of the live audience will be drawn from people who follow @whitehouse and sign up on whitehouse.gov/tweetup. The White House uses Twitter to share news and updates with its 2.25 million followers and to engage with the public on various issues.